# LAB 02 — VLANs and Trunking

## Overview
This lab demonstrates how VLANs operate across multiple switches using trunk links (802.1Q). It simulates a real enterprise network where departments span multiple floors.

## Objectives
- Configure VLANs on multiple switches
- Assign access ports to VLANs
- Configure trunk links between switches
- Allow VLANs to pass between switches
- Verify and test VLAN isolation

## Topology
- 2 Switches (SW1, SW2)
- 6 PCs
- 1 trunk link between switches

## VLANs
- VLAN 10: HR
- VLAN 20: IT
- VLAN 30: Sales

## Key Concepts
- Access vs Trunk ports
- VLAN tagging (802.1Q)
- Inter-switch VLAN communication

## Verification
- show vlan brief
- show interfaces trunk
- Ping tests between hosts

## Result
Same VLAN devices communicate across switches, while different VLANs remain isolated.
